'''Lithoautotrophy''' is a special type of [[chemotroph|chemoautotrophy]] found exclusively in [[Archaea]] and [[Bacteria]]. Lithoautotrophic organisms utilize [[inorganic]] compounds as energy sources, typically from mineral in origin. The word ''lithoautotrophy'' means "to feed it- or oneself from stone". In ancient Greek, ''lithos'' means stone or rock, ''autos'' means self, and ''trophein'' to feed.

