{{The Works of Aristotle}}
'''''Movement of Animals''''' (or '''''On the Motion of Animals'''''; Greek Περὶ ζῴων κινήσεως; Latin ''De Motu Animalium'') is one of [[Aristotle]]'s major [[Aristotle's biology|texts on biology]]. It sets out the general principles of [[animal locomotion]].

