{{About|a structure created by worms|information about worm castings ([[excretion]]) used in gardening |vermicomposting}}
[[File:Lugworm cast, Red Wharf Bay, Isle of Anglesey - geograph.org.uk - 30354.jpg|thumb|[[Lugworm]] cast, Red Wharf Bay, Isle of Anglesey]]

A '''worm cast''' is a structure created by [[worm]]s, typically on [[soils]] such as those on [[beach]]es <ref name=BBC>[http://www.open2.net/coast/postcard_beachlife.html BBC Beach Life]</ref><ref name=wir>[http://www.wirral.gov.uk/er/nwcp_intertidal.htm North Wirral - Intertidal Habitats]</ref> that gives the appearance of multiple worms.

